Update a4GATE Hostname
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Dashboard" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
The a4GATE hostname needs to be the same for both, Data Collector and Data
Sender. If that's not the case, a red text will appear as shown in the figure:
4
Enter the serial number "S/N" on the side of the device as a4GATE host name.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
The serial number of the a4gate is also entered so that the device can be traced
back correctly during troubleshooting should problems arise, as well as always
having the ability to figure out which device is being worked on.
5
Click the "Save" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
6
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
After you have received a green feedback, you have to reboot both a4GATE PCs.
You can press the physical "power" button of a4GATE and wait until all lights go
out. Now you can switch on the a4GATE again.
